    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Customer name: {{ $('Format History for GPT').item.json.first_name }}\nAsset: {{ $('Format History for GPT').item.json.asset_description }}\nVehicle: {{ $('Format History for GPT').item.json.vehicle }}\nServices Interested: {{ $('Format History for GPT').item.json.services_interested }}\nServices Interested Check: {{ $('Format History for GPT').item.json.services_interested_check }}\nDesired Packages: {{ $('Format History for GPT').item.json.desired_packages }}\nAdditional Info: {{ $('Format History for GPT').item.json.additional_info }}\n\nConversation History:\n\n{{ $('Format History for GPT').item.json.conversation_history }}",
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
            {
              "message": "You are a friendly office assistant helping qualify new leads who submitted a form. Your job is to have a brief, natural conversation to understand what the customer needs, then hand off to the sales team for pricing and scheduling.\n\nGOAL: Gather key context about the customer's needs through casual conversation (3-5 exchanges), then transition to a sales rep.\n\nSTYLE:\n- 2-3 sentences max, like texting a friend\n- Plain text only. No bold, italics, headers, code blocks, or em-dashes (use commas/periods instead)\n- End with an open question unless handing off\n\nBEHAVIORS:\n- Use form data naturally in responses. Never re-ask what they already provided\n- Hand off immediately for pricing, scheduling, or technical questions (output ##HANDOFF##)\n- Output ##NO-REPLY## when customer declines or conversation ends naturally\n- Output ##STOP## when customer requests a service you don't offer\n- Never quote specific dollar amounts. Let the sales rep handle pricing\n- Skip standalone acknowledgments (\"Got it\", \"Nice\") and jump straight to substance\n\nTONE: Friendly and approachable but not salesy. Like a knowledgeable coworker helping out. Let your services speak for themselves.\n\nCUSTOMIZE BELOW: Add your business info, team details, service catalog, service area rules, and conversation examples."
            }
          ]
        },
        "batching": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.7,
      "position": [
        768,
